</head><body><table width=90% align=center><tr><td class=textbody><center><h1>Lvl 51-54: Cobalt Scar</h1><br>by Shafli Tritium</center><br><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse: collapse" bordercolor="#111111" width="531" id="AutoNumber1">
  <tr>
    <td width="531"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana">
    <font color="#FFFFFF"><b>51-54, Cobalt Scar</b></font><br>
    Minimum Level: 51<br>
    Maximum Level: 54<br>
    Zone Name: Cobalt Scar<br>
    Camp Area/LOC: Next to the TP ring<br>
    Mob List (HP): Wyverns<br>
    Availability (1-&gt;10): 2<br>
    Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 7 (they drop gems)<br>
    Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 3 (just avoid the named)<br>
    Faction Affected: COV on named Yvolcarm<br>
    <br>
    Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: Often camped but very easy, Wyverns will not agro 
    if you have a good faction with Claws of Veeshan, except for Yvolcarm and 
    Azureake (the named Cobalt Drake). So stay away from them when they are up, 
    they are not snarable neither rootable. Killing them will decrease your CoV 
    faction. If you aggro, just run and then gate. Need to be Dubious to CoV to 
    travel safely here. </span>
    <p><font size="2"><span style="font-family: Verdana">Note from Gemdiver: The 
    best way to quad here is to pull wyverns down the cliff onto the beach with 
    your temp flux staff. Providing you have good faction with the otters, this 
    gives the minimal chance of adds. </span></font></p>
    <p><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana"><![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]>
